<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-235-372  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 235 372.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telecommuting Review: the Gordon Report  March 1 1990 v7 n3 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Union won't appeal court ruling on homework regulations.andO;(International Ladies Garment Workers Union, Federal DistrictCourt)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Department of Labor released the final rules on the control ofhome-based work in the garment industry late in 1988.andP;  TheInternational Ladies Garment Workers Union (ILGWU) and two otherunions filed suit in Jan 1989 to overturn the regulations,claiming they would not adequately protect the worker againstexploitation and that they threaten to lower the standards inother industries.andP;  A Federal district court judge ruled in Dec1989 that the rules, which called for Labor Departmentcertification and monitoring by inspectors, represented areasonable approach.andP;  The Union has since dropped the suit sayingthat the nature of the Judge's decision did not make thelikelihood for success very great.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     TelecommutingLegal IssuesWork at HomeCourt CasesUnionsUnited States. Department of LaborRegulation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>